===Etymology===
Latin ''alopecia'', from the Greek ''alopexia'', (fox-mange), from ''alopex'', (fox) + ''-ia'', (a formative ending used in Greek, esp. used in naming diseases)

===Noun===
'''alopecia'''
{{wikipedia}}
#[[Bald]]ness.
#''Pathol.'' [[Deficiency]] of the hair, may be caused by [[failure]] to grow or loss after growth
#''Med.'' [[Loss]] of hair (especially on the head) or loss of wool or feathers, which either happens naturally or is caused by disease

